The paper deals with the evaluation of human ability to detect doctored images, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the study involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) since it evaluates how users interact with images and provide evidence of their judgments. The use of forensic databases and the analysis of user features suggest a connection to multimedia (cs.MM), computer security (cs.CR), and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
